    "## Step 6: Data Cleaning and Unit Conversion\n",
    "\n",
    "Military statistics often include **units, commas, or textual formatting** that cannot be directly used for numerical analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "Examples include:\n",
    "\n",
    "- \"1,234 units\"\n",
    "- \"3.5 million\"\n",
    "- \"250+ aircraft\"\n",
    "\n",
    "To ensure consistency, a **custom unit parsing function** is implemented to:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Remove commas and special characters\n",
    "- Convert text values into numerical format\n",
    "- Standardize units across different metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "This cleaning process ensures that all extracted values can be used for **quantitative analysis and visualization**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "81af08cd-5662-4162-9f49-671ac66fd661",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Unit Parser\n",
    "def unit(raw_text):\n",
    "    if raw_text is None:\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "\n",
    "    text = raw_text.replace(\",\", \"\").strip()\n",
    "\n",
    "    number_match = re.search(r\"[\\d.]+\", text)\n",
    "    number = number_match.group() if number_match else \"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    unit_match = re.search(r\"[a-zA-Z%./]+\", text)\n",
    "    unit = unit_match.group() if unit_match else \"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    return f\"{number} {unit}\".strip()"
   ]
  },
